AFAIK, onnxruntime works well with gcc 4.8.5. I haven't tried gcc 4.8.4. It failed because it can't recognize the macro POPULATE_OP_DOC_STR @pranavsharma  FYI.

> AFAIK, onnxruntime works well with gcc 4.8.5. I haven't tried gcc 4.8.4. It failed because it can't recognize the macro POPULATE_OP_DOC_STR @pranavsharma FYI.

The introduction of the POPULATE_OP_DOC_STR macro along with string literals surfaced a [compiler bug](https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=55971) that got [fixed](https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=57620) only in gcc 4.9.0 and after.

well, i simply delete all the linefeed in the POPULATE_OP_DOC_STR doc definition and it works, just like this:
old:
```
POPULATE_OP_DOC_STR(doc=R"aaa
bbb
ccc";);
```
new:
```
POPULATE_OP_DOC_STR(doc=R"aaa bbb ccc";);
```

it seems gcc4.8.4 can't handle multi line raw string lol

thanks for your help~
